---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import CTA from "../components/CTA.astro";
---

<Layout title="Contact">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="shell page-hero__body">
      <div class="page-hero__text">
        <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
        <h1 class="headline-xl">Request an Agent Behavior & Control Review.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          If your agents are moving from demo to production, Semantiv can help
          you understand their behavior, model what their work means, and design
          controls before deployment scales.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="button button--primary" href="mailto:hello@semantiv.ai?subject=Agent%20Behavior%20%26%20Control%20Review">Email hello@semantiv.ai</a>
          <a class="button button--secondary" href="/review">Review the offer</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-hero__meta">
        <p>Best first conversation: one workflow where the agent is useful, risky, and hard to explain.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">01 Send</div>
      <div class="section-body split">
        <div>
          <h2 class="headline-lg">Send a short note with the workflow and the risk.</h2>
          <p class="lede">
            A clear starting point is better than a complete system inventory.
            Semantiv can begin with the traces and artifacts you already have.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="rule-list">
          <li><code>01</code><span>What your agents do.</span></li>
          <li><code>02</code><span>What tools, systems, data, or documents they touch.</span></li>
          <li><code>03</code><span>Which actions or decisions create the most risk.</span></li>
          <li><code>04</code><span>What traces, logs, workflows, or artifacts exist today.</span></li>
          <li><code>05</code><span>Where approvals or controls currently happen.</span></li>
          <li><code>06</code><span>Whether contracts, policies, or regulated documents are involved.</span></li>
          <li><code>07</code><span>Whether you want review, architecture, prototype, or implementation support.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <div class="section-label">02 Design partners</div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <h2 class="headline-lg">Semantiv is especially interested in agents that already interact with high-trust operations.</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          Production tools, code, customer workflows, regulated data, contracts,
          financial records, healthcare operations, and approval-heavy documents
          are strong starting points.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    title="Send your agent workflow."
    copy="Use hello@semantiv.ai and include one concrete workflow, the tools it touches, and the decision you need to trust."
    primaryHref="mailto:hello@semantiv.ai?subject=Agent%20workflow%20for%20Semantiv"
    primaryLabel="Send your agent workflow"
    secondaryHref="/method"
    secondaryLabel="See the method"
  />
</Layout>
